column11: Saw queen, fine amount of brood. haven't really built too much on the foundation frames. Replace the top brood box's filler frame with foundation, put it two frames from the right, seeing as the queen was a bit more active in that region
Hive action

They technically had enough space if you look at the amount of bees. But they clearly didn't have enough space for brood and started filling potential-drone-area with honey. So added a super.
And lowered the filler frames from 4 to 2. Now there is a one filler frame on the right of each brood box

column11: Active inside but not aggressive, added a box, 4 filler frames (one on each side), pulled up 2 frames (one with queen) and filled the rest with spare frames from dead hive. Queen excluder between them (with the 2nd entrance)
